SENATE RESOLUTION 261
By Walley
A RESOLUTION to honor Jennifer Channell of Hardin County
upon her receipt of the TSSAA Distinguished
Service Award.
WHEREAS, the members of this legislative body are pleased to recognize those
individuals whose dedication, integrity, and service have brought honor to the State of
Tennessee and whose leadership has positively shaped the lives of young people; and
WHEREAS, one such remarkable leader is Jennifer Channell, longtime bowling coach at
Hardin County High School, who recently received the prestigious Tennessee Secondary
School Athletic Association (TSSAA) Distinguished Service Award in recognition of her
extraordinary contributions to interscholastic athletics; and
WHEREAS, for more than two decades, Coach Channell has guided the bowling
program at her alma mater, Hardin County High School, helping to build one of the most
successful dynasties in Tennessee high school sports history; and
WHEREAS, under Coach Channell's leadership, Hardin County High School has
captured sixteen TSSAA State Bowling Championships, including twelve consecutive titles, a
record of sustained excellence that reflects her dedication, discipline, and commitment to
student athlete development; and
WHEREAS, Coach Jennifer Channell's guidance has extended far beyond competition,
as she has helped countless students grow in confidence, responsibility, and perseverance,
instilling values that will guide them long after their time in high school athletics has ended; and
WHEREAS, a strong advocate for opportunity through sport, Jennifer Channell has
helped many of her student athletes continue their education through collegiate bowling
scholarships, opening doors for academic and personal advancement; and
SR0261
011343
- 1 -

WHEREAS, her own family reflects the power of her example, as her daughters earned
bowling scholarships, her oldest daughter, Ashley, receiving a scholarship to Louisiana Tech
University, and her younger daughter, Kailee, garnering a scholarship to Vanderbilt University,
where she helped her teammates claim an NCAA National Championship; and
WHEREAS, through tireless work, thoughtful mentorship, and unwavering belief in her
athletes, Coach Channell has transformed bowling from a school activity into a pathway of
opportunity for young Tennesseans; and
WHEREAS, Jennifer Channell epitomizes the spirit and commitment that are
characteristic of a true Tennessean; and
WHEREAS, we find it appropriate to acknowledge and applaud Coach Channell for her
many contributions to high school athletics in Tennessee; now, therefore,
BE IT RESOLVED BY THE SENATE OF THE ONE HUNDRED FOURTEENTH
GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF TENNESSEE, that we honor and commend
Jennifer Channell upon her receipt of the TSSAA Distinguished Service Award and extend to
her our best wishes for much continued success in all her future endeavors.
BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED, that an appropriate copy of this resolution be prepared
for presentation with this final clause omitted from such copy.
